The Steward’s Mandate: Correcting the User-Experience Error1. The Delusion of OwnershipHumanity incorrectly views itself as the "owner" of the Earth.  This belief creates the false sense that our "maintenance contract" is optional.  This mindset inevitably leads to exploitation, pollution, and the conversion of our shared home into a Kuppai Medu (garbage heap).  2. The Reality: We are Transient GuidesIn truth, we are not owners; we are transient beings and guides on this planet.  Our purpose is to facilitate proper development and maintain the environment for those who follow.  We are stewards of a "Universal Rented Room," and our stay is temporary.  3. The Maintenance ContractBecause we are stewards, we have no right to breach our maintenance obligations.  Every act of pollution is a direct violation of the terms of our "stay".  Success is not measured by personal power or wealth, but by the condition of the space we leave behind for the next arrival.  
